A Rongai matatu on Saturday was &nbsp;burnt down for hitting and killing child cycling on Lang'ata Road. The matatu, KCB 632R &nbsp;is said to have been driven in the wrong lane when the accident happened. Nairobi police boss Koome said he will address the issue once he gets details of the accident that took place opposite Uhuru gardens. Last year four&nbsp; people died and six others were injured after a matatu veered off the road and overturned on Lang&rsquo;ata Road. Read:&nbsp; Four dead, 6 injured in Lang'ata road accidentKinyanjui was charged on Monday with five counts of causing by dangerous driving.More on this:&nbsp; Killer Rongai matatu driver granted Sh1 million bond, held 14 days&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;